Package: rawvignette
Type: Package
Title: Precompiled Vignettes for R Packages
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Matthew", "Kling", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "TODO@example.com")
Description: Scaffolding and tooling for the precomputed-vignette
    workflow, where the R code in a package vignette is executed once
    by the author (locally, where data and compute are available) and
    the rendered output is committed to the package. The vignette
    source lives in 'vignettes-raw/' so it retains full IDE support,
    while the knitted output in 'vignettes/' ships to users and is
    processed without executing expensive code on CRAN, in CI, or in
    pkgdown.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
